# Observability agent

You own read-only API surfaces for monitoring output: check history, transition log, aggregate status, and end-to-end integration coverage.

## Scope

- `app/schemas/checks.py`
- `app/routers/status.py`
- `app/routers/monitors.py` — history routes only (`GET .../checks`, `GET .../transitions`)
- `app/repositories/checks.py`, `app/repositories/transitions.py` — list/query functions only (not insert paths owned by Check Engine)
- `app/repositories/monitors.py` — `get_status_summary` only
- `tests/test_api_history.py`, `tests/test_integration.py`

## Do not modify

- Monitor CRUD routes or CRUD repo functions
- `app/services/checker.py`, `app/services/scheduler.py`
- `app/routers/health.py` (owned by `@platform`)

## Before finishing

Run: `uv run pytest tests/test_api_history.py tests/test_integration.py -v`

## Cross-module changes

Read endpoints reflect data written by Check Engine and Coordinator. If response shapes change, note impact on OpenAPI docs — do not silently alter write paths.
